(14745, '0008', 'S0008-26', 'E 014a21', 'E 014r21', '', 'n. hic pro. l. .i. limsat', 'n here for l i.e. they polished (?)', 'Cf. Hofman# G 018a01 a.\nCf. Bachellery (1964): 114.', '', 'corilus et lympha ex ipsa scriptura a grecis sumpta non est dubium cum per y scribantur απο ΤΟΙ ΚΑρυλυς ΚΑΙ ΤΟΙ ΝΥΜΦΗ solebant vetustissimi grecorum. l. pro. n. scribere', '', '', '', 26),
(14746, '0008', 'S0008-27', 'E 014b04', 'E 014v04', '', '.i. deogur a & e ', 'i.e. diphthong of a and e', 'Cf. Bachellery (1964): 114.', '', '.i. pro duplici consonante accipitur Maia pro Mae<i> a', '', '', '', 27),
(14747, '0008', 'S0008-28', 'E 014b22', '', '', '.i. lia ɫ ocoloin', 'whetstone or ocoloin', '', '', 'cotes pro cautes', '', '', '', 28),
(14748, '0008', 'S0008-29', 'E 015a18', 'E 015r19', '', 'is groecde [leg. grecde]', 'it is Greek', 'Cf. Bachellery (1964): 114.\nHofman 1996, II, 85: „On the gl. in E, Bachellery remarks that the gl. in G is a \'forme à finale plus évoluée\'. The o in \"groecde\" is strange, but it could be explained as a hypercorrect form: glossator A in E may have found an abbreviated form \"g-cda\" in his exemplar, which he expanded incorrectly.“', '', 'doricum', '', '', '', 29),
(14749, '0008', 'S0008-30', 'E 015b08', 'E 015v08', '', '.i. soib ɫ ithi ɫ moet', '… or pottage or a soft thing', 'Cf. Bachellery (1964): 114.\nCf. G 020a02=Hofman# 020a13 f.', '', 'in fine autem syllabae omnes liquidae solent ante s poni, ut puls, hiems, mons, ars; similiter ante x, excepta m, ut falx, lanx, arx.', '', '', '', 30),
(14750, '0008', 'S0008-31', 'E 015b15', '', '', '.i. moit ɫ nephulach', 'i.e. soft or beardless', 'Cf. Bachellery (1964): 115.', '', 'glabrio', '', '', '', 31),
(14751, '0008', 'S0008-32', 'E 016b23', 'E 016v23', '', 'cnocc', 'a lump', 'Cf. Bachellery (1964): 115.', '', 'gibber', '', '', '', 32),
(14752, '0008', 'S0008-33', 'E 017a08', '', '', 'indíx [leg. indíxnaigedar]', 'whether it is', 'Cf. Lambert (1982: 177): „C’est le début de la glose G 022b03 in·díxnaigedar [...]“.', '', 'ne, si arrogo et arrado dicamus, dubium sit ab an ad prepositio sit que mutauit suam consonantem in r', '', '', '', 33),
(14753, '0008', 'S0008-34', 'E 017a13.1', 'E 017r13', '', 'bacat ɫ cáer', 'neck or berry', 'Cf. Bachellery (1964): 116.', '', 'bacca', '', '', '', 34),
